			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> paper:</span><br><i>Integration of Data Validation and User Interface Concerns in a DSL for Web Applications</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/DannyMGroenewegen.html">Danny M. Groenewegen</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_13">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_13</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> The paper presents a DSL that integrates validation and UI concerns for web applications.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> Its main idea is integrating multiple concerns (data validation + UI) in one language.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> A key motivation is improving the developer/user interaction with forms and validation feedback (usability).
</li></ul></li></ul>
